<br>
There are 2 known places to get your green scale, Sev and Hoskar. Hoskar in VP requires a decent size guild to get to, not to mention the pain of keying your members.<br>
<br>
Sev is very difficult to catch up and you need to be able to mobilize your members quickly enough to kill him. <br>
<br>
We now have whats affectionately called the Manaburn Crew on my server, that for the most part, has started to farm Sev and his precious scale. Average going price for it is between 80 and 100k.<br>
<br>
Is this good or bad? Its tough enough to catch the guy up as it is now, without having to contend with 5 or 6 wizards, being able to burn him down. On the other hand it makes the scale more accessible to those that may or may not ever get a shot at one. <br>
<br>
Was wondering what your thoughts are on this?<br>
<br>
Dentarg DeBasher<br>
60 Warlord <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/upag0.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pag0</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 94<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/18/02 3:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=542.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.fallenalliance.org/screenshots/downwpst.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Green Scale, is this Good or Bad ?</span><hr size=1> old topic. numerous threads on it.<br>
