<br>
Heck, the only time a wizard (or druid) is wanted in an exp group is if evac is necessary.  Otherwise most groups would rather replace him/her with a damage dealing rogue or monk, although with the new pet aggro changes I've seen mages and necros getting more attraction (which is great imho).<br>
<br>
Now the fact that warriors have a rough mob is terrible, but lets talk about a few other classes epics, namely clerics and rage fire in Skyfire, now there's some competition.  Or how about VS in KC for being highly competitive.<br>
<br>
Worse epic mobs I can think of are the ones that are random spawns in dungeons or parts of dungeons that are seldom camped.  Try boring a group or two groups of people to death trying to get your epic mob to spawn.  I mention Chardok for the monks and necros.  <br>
<br>
Even worse yet, is PoA for Mages, you have to get all the way to 7th isle which is a two day raid for most guilds.  Try and get that kind of commitment, only to find out that the mage epic piece is an uncommon drop.  Lovely.  Maybe turns into a 3 day raid....<br>
<br>
Or this is one of my favorites, although an easy mob to kill and in a newbie zone, a random spawn epic mob that can spawn in any part of the zone (quillmane) and drops the epic piece to a class that doesn't have the track ability.  That's just plain silly.  Or even more ludicrous is that a low level player can solo it, but can't help MQ the no drop piece until they reach lvl 46.  What a waste.  The rangers should have an epic piece drop off of that stupid mob, not mages.<br>
